    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1448576137" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1448576137" />
    <a title="Farren" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/29738019-farren"><img alt="Farren" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1438296630p2/29738019.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1448576137?book_show_action=true">Oct 04, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Farren" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Farren" href="/user/show/29738019-farren">Farren</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29738019-farren?shelf=holy-cover-batman">holy-cover-batman</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29738019-farren?shelf=fantasy-paranormal">fantasy-paranormal</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1448576137" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9880796757662547267">Poor writing, boring characters, and inane world building, unfortunately none of which are enough to cover the fact that the plot is little more than a series of sexual encounters. The reader is endlessly told <i>what</i> their community is like but never any good reasons <i>why</i>. I listened to the audiobook and without even reading a physical copy I could tell this is some self-published Amazon freebie, verified by the fact that so many reviews mention a ton of spelling and grammar errors in their ebooks.</span>
  <span id="freeText9880796757662547267" style="display:none">Poor writing, boring characters, and inane world building, unfortunately none of which are enough to cover the fact that the plot is little more than a series of sexual encounters. The reader is endlessly told <i>what</i> their community is like but never any good reasons <i>why</i>. I listened to the audiobook and without even reading a physical copy I could tell this is some self-published Amazon freebie, verified by the fact that so many reviews mention a ton of spelling and grammar errors in their ebooks. I appreciate that the author did not force a romance between the two narrators, but I also recognize that it's so she can give the bad boy a cliche redemption arc. I'm just not getting all the glowing reviews, as almost every other fantasy book (my favorite genre) that I've ever read has been better than this...</span>
  <a data-text-id="9880796757662547267" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

