<span id="freeTextContainer14436169044352449634">Generally, this sort of teen/YA paranormal genre doesn&apos;t appeal to me, but I liked the poetic title and the gorgeous cover, so I gave it a chance. It starts out with a flash and peters out until near the end. But the characters are fleshed out and the world building is done pretty well. I&apos;m so glad there was no love triangle in this one. I&apos;m not a fan of the alternating first person POV, but this might be because I listened to it.<br/><br/>Pamela Lorence does a really great job narrating. The female voice</span>
  <span id="freeText14436169044352449634" style="display:none">Generally, this sort of teen/YA paranormal genre doesn't appeal to me, but I liked the poetic title and the gorgeous cover, so I gave it a chance. It starts out with a flash and peters out until near the end. But the characters are fleshed out and the world building is done pretty well. I'm so glad there was no love triangle in this one. I'm not a fan of the alternating first person POV, but this might be because I listened to it.<br /><br />Pamela Lorence does a really great job narrating. The female voices sounded very good for the characters and her pacing was fantastic.<br /><br />**I received a copy of this book in exchange for an honest review.**</span>
